# Terraform Provider Setup

This project demonstrates how to configure and initialize Terraform providers for Infrastructure as Code (IaC) deployments.

---

## 🚀 Overview

The purpose of this project is to learn and practice:

- Terraform provider configuration
- Azure Provider setup
- Terraform initialization
- Infrastructure as Code basics
- Terraform workflow commands

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Terraform
- Microsoft Azure
- Azure CLI
- Git & GitHub

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```bash
terraform-provider-setup/
│
├── provider.tf
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Provider Configuration

This project uses the AzureRM provider.

Example:

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    azurerm = {
      source  = "hashicorp/azurerm"
      version = "~> 4.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "azurerm" {
  features {}
}
```

---

## 🚀 Terraform Commands

### Initialize Terraform

```bash
terraform init
```

### Validate Configuration

```bash
terraform validate
```

### Format Code

```bash
terraform fmt
```

